{"title_page": "Scott Feschuk", "text_new": "'''Scott Feschuk''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] speechwriter, humorist and former newspaper journalist.\n\nHis journalism career began at ''[[The Globe and Mail]]''. After five years as a TV and political columnist for the ''[[National Post]]'', he left the newspaper in 2004 to become chief speechwriter for then [[Prime Minister of Canada|Prime Minister]] [[Paul Martin]],\n\nAfter working for a year or so on the writing staff of the [[CBC Television]] show ''[[This Hour Has 22 Minutes]]'', he wrote the books ''Searching for Michael Jackson's Nose''<ref>{{cite book|title=Searching for Michael Jackson's Nose|url=https://archive.org/details/searchingformich0000fesc|url-access=registration|publisher=McClelland & Stewart|year=2003}}</ref> and ''How Not to Completely Suck as a New Parent''<ref>{{cite book|title=How Not to Completely Suck as a New Parent|publisher=McClelland & Stewart|year=2004}}</ref> and currently writes a humour column in the Canadian magazine ''[[Maclean's]]'' and a blog on the ''Maclean''s'' website.\n\nDuring the [[2006 Canadian federal election|2006 federal election]], Feschuk wrote a popular daily [[blog]] about life on the campaign trail. After the Liberal defeat in the election, he formed a speechwriting company called Feschuk.Reid, along with [[Scott Reid (political advisor)|Scott Reid]], one of Prime Minister Martin's senior advisors.\n\nHe has written extensively on television and film. One time, after the [[Academy Awards|Oscars]], [[Faye Dunaway]] mistook him for a valet and ordered him to find her limo.{{citation needed|date=November 2014}}\n\nHe was formerly the editor of [[UWO Gazette|the ''Gazette'']] at the [[University of Western Ontario]]. He is currently employed by [[Huawei]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/chinas-offensive-on-canada-in-plain-sight/|title=China's offensive on Canada, in plain sight|last=Glavin|first=Terry|date=May 17, 2019|website=[[Maclean's]]|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> His younger brother Dave is a sportswriter for the ''[[Toronto Star]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://archive.is/20061006005708/http://forums.macleans.ca/advansis/?mod=for&act=dis&eid=13 Scott Feschuk]\n* [http://feschuk-reid.com/ Feschuk Reid]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Feschuk, Scott}}\n[[Category:Canadian humour columnists]]\n[[Category:Canadian political consultants]]\n[[Category:Canadian bloggers]]\n[[Category:University of Western Ontario alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Speechwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian newspaper journalists]]\n[[Category:Canadian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Male bloggers]]\n", "text_old": "'''Scott Feschuk''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] speechwriter, humorist and former newspaper journalist.\n\nHis journalism career began at ''[[The Globe and Mail]]''. After five years as a TV and political columnist for the ''[[National Post]]'', he left the newspaper in 2004 to become chief speechwriter for then [[Prime Minister of Canada|Prime Minister]] [[Paul Martin]],\n\nAfter working for a year or so on the writing staff of the [[CBC Television]] show ''[[This Hour Has 22 Minutes]]'', he wrote the books ''Searching for Michael Jackson's Nose''<ref>{{cite book|title=Searching for Michael Jackson's Nose|url=https://archive.org/details/searchingformich0000fesc|url-access=registration|publisher=McClelland & Stewart|year=2003}}</ref> and ''How Not to Completely Suck as a New Parent''<ref>{{cite book|title=How Not to Completely Suck as a New Parent|publisher=McClelland & Stewart|year=2004}}</ref> and currently writes a humour column in the Canadian magazine ''[[Maclean's]]'' and a blog on the ''Maclean''s'' website.\n\nDuring the [[2006 Canadian federal election|2006 federal election]], Feschuk wrote a popular daily [[blog]] about life on the campaign trail. After the Liberal defeat in the election, he formed a speechwriting company called Feschuk.Reid, along with [[Scott Reid (political advisor)|Scott Reid]], one of Prime Minister Martin's senior advisors.\n\nHe has written extensively on television and film. One time, after the [[Academy Awards|Oscars]], [[Faye Dunaway]] mistook him for a valet and ordered him to find her limo.{{citation needed|date=November 2014}}\n\nHe was formerly the editor of [[UWO Gazette|the ''Gazette'']] at the [[University of Western Ontario]]. He is currently employed by [[Huawei]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macleans.ca/politics/ottawa/chinas-offensive-on-canada-in-plain-sight/|title=China's offensive on Canada, in plain sight|last=Glavin|first=Terry|date=May 17, 2019|website=[[Maclean's]]|access-date=2019-08-04}}</ref> His younger brother Dave is a sportswriter for the ''[[Toronto Star]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://archive.is/20061006005708/http://forums.macleans.ca/advansis/?mod=for&act=dis&eid=13 Scott Feschuk]\n* [http://feschuk-reid.com/ Feschuk Reid]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Feschuk, Scott}}\n[[Category:Canadian humour columnists]]\n[[Category:Canadian political consultants]]\n[[Category:Canadian bloggers]]\n[[Category:University of Western Ontario alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Speechwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian newspaper journalists]]\n[[Category:Canadian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Male bloggers]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scott_Feschuk"}
